Also, if SCP-1777-2 hasn't necessarily demonstrated any anomalous properties and isn't really contained, I personally doubt it would be classified as an SCP. And, in my mind, they'd list the sword as  rather than classifying it as an SCP before deciding whether or not it's anomalous.

As for the concept hm. It's an interesting idea, but it's not really working for me in this form. I can't tell if it's because of the execution or just the concept butting up against the SCP format. On the whole, I don't particularly like this, so Imma downvote.

Also, formalized the footnotes into Wikidot formatting. Now you can hover over the numbers and shit, it's p. neat.

